            "type": "text",
            "title": "Numbers in Python 🔢",
            "content": "# Two Main Number Types\n\nPython has two main types of numbers:\n\n* **int** (Integer) — Whole numbers\n  * `42`, `-17`, `0`, `1000000`\n* **float** (Floating-point) — Decimal numbers\n  * `3.14`, `-0.5`, `2.0`, `99.99`\n\nPython handles the type automatically!"
