            "title": "Augmented Assignment 📝",
            "content": "# Shortcut Operators\n\nInstead of writing `x = x + 5`, use shortcuts:\n\n| Long form | Shortcut |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `x = x + 5` | `x += 5` |\n| `x = x - 5` | `x -= 5` |\n| `x = x * 5` | `x *= 5` |\n| `x = x / 5` | `x /= 5` |\n\nSaves typing and is cleaner!"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_16",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Shortcuts in Action 💻",
            "content": "See augmented assignment operators:",
            "codeSnippet": "score = 100\nprint(\"Start:\", score)\n\nscore += 50  # Add 50\nprint(\"After +=50:\", score)\n\nscore -= 30  # Subtract 30\nprint(\"After -=30:\", score)\n\nscore *= 2   # Double it\nprint(\"After *=2:\", score)",
